@startuml bb84-protocol
!include style.puml

title BB84 Quantum Key Distribution Protocol

participant "Alice\n(Sender)" as A $GREEN
participant "Quantum Channel\n(Fiber)" as QC $YELLOW
participant "Bob\n(Receiver)" as B $BLUE
participant "Classical Channel\n(Authenticated)" as CC $GRAY

== Step 1: Quantum Transmission ==

A -> A : Generate random bits\n{0, 1, 1, 0, 1, 0, ...}
A -> A : Choose random bases\n{+, x, +, x, x, +, ...}
A -> QC : Encode bits as polarized photons\n(H/V for + basis, D/A for x basis)
note right of QC : Poisson-distributed\nphoton pulses (μ ≈ 0.1)\nwith fiber attenuation

QC -> B : Photons arrive at SPD
B -> B : Choose random bases\n{x, x, +, +, x, +, ...}
B -> B : Measure each photon\nin chosen basis

== Step 2: Sifting ==

B -> CC : Send Bob's basis choices
CC -> A : (publicly visible)
A -> CC : Send Alice's basis choices
CC -> B : (publicly visible)
A -> A : Keep only matching-basis bits
B -> B : Keep only matching-basis bits

note over A, B : ~50% of detected bits survive sifting

== Step 3: QBER Estimation ==

A -> CC : Reveal 10% sample of sifted bits
CC -> B :
B -> B : Compare with own bits\nCount mismatches
B -> CC : Report QBER

alt QBER > 11% (Eavesdropper Detected)
    B -> CC : **ABORT** — key compromised
    CC -> A :
    A -> A : Discard key material
    B -> B : Discard key material
    note over A, B $RED : Restart protocol\nwith new random bits
else QBER < 11% (Secure)
    note over A, B $GREEN : Channel is secure\nProceed to error correction
end

== Step 4: Error Correction (Cascade) ==

A -> CC : Block parities (Pass 1)
CC -> B :
B -> B : Compare parities\nBinary search for errors
B -> CC : Request sub-block parities
CC -> A :
note over A, B : Repeat with doubled block size\nfor 4 passes

== Step 5: Privacy Amplification ==

A -> CC : Random Toeplitz matrix seed
CC -> B :
A -> A : Hash corrected key\n(removes Eve's information)
B -> B : Hash corrected key\n(same Toeplitz matrix)

note over A, B $GREEN : **Final shared key**\n128 bits, information-theoretically secure

@enduml
